  "text": "Myocardium density was set to 1.053 g/ml following the methodology used in several publications on either rats [CITATION_1] or human [CITATION_2] . Following data from the literature (ASM International, 2009), the pledget was setup as an elastic material with a density of 2 g/cm 3 and a Young Modulus of 550 MPa. Suture wire material data were extracted from the literature [CITATION_3] , density was set to 0.403 g/cm 3 and Young Modulus to 745.6 MPa.",
